k—even though it doesn't feel like a movement away. [For example,] an iPhone can only be changed by Steve Jobs or soon, with the software development kit, by programmers that he personally approves that go through his iPhone apps store. Or whimsical applications that run on the Facebook platform or the new Google apps. These are controllable by their vendors in ways that Bill Gates never dreamed of controlling Windows applications. [...] That's the ironic thing. Bill Gates is Mr. Proprietary. But for my purposes, even under the standard Windows operating system from 1990, 1991, you write the code, you can hand it to somebody else and they can run it. Bill Gates has nothing to say about it. So it's funny to think that by moving in Steve Jobs's direction it actually ends up far more proprietary.\n- ^ Johnston, Michael. Do iPhone Hacks Void Your Warranty?. iPhone Alley. 2007-10-20 [2009-05-14]. （原始内容存档于2010-06-07）.\n- ^ Moren, Dan. iPhone hackers look to an uncertain future. Macworld. 2008-05-28 [2009-05-25]. （原始内容存档于2009-06-08）.\n- ^ FAQ Details （页面存档备份，存于互联网档案馆）. Eshop.macsales.com（March 27, 2013）. Retrieved on July 30, 2013.\n- ^ set restrictions. Imore.com. 2009-04-13 [2012-10-25]. （原始内容存档于2012-10-28）.\n- ^ IOS Understanding Restrictions. Apple Inc. Apple Inc. [2012-09-26]. （原始内容存档于2012-10-02）.\n- ^ Johansen, Jon Lech. iPhone Independence Day. nanocr.eu. 2007-07-03 [2008-06-06]. （原始内容存档于2008-06-02）.\n- ^ iPhone 3G. Apple Store (UK). [2009-05-14]. （原始内容存档于2009-06-04）.\n- ^ Apple —iPhone —Buy iPhone 3G. Apple Inc. [2009-06-14]. （原始内容存档于2009-06-27）.[查证请求]\n- ^ 乔布斯为iPhone降价致歉 承诺对老用户作出补偿 （页面存档备份，存于互联网档案馆），新华网\n- ^ 联通澄清：iPhone目前不带Wi-Fi. 驱动之家. 2009-12-05 [2009-12-18]. （原始内容存档于2009-12-08） （中文（中国大陆））.\n- ^ iPhone5为何只在中国涨价. tech.sina.com.cn. [2018-08-05]. （原始内容存档于2018-08-05）.\n- ^ iPhone 7 / 7 Plus 各国售价对比（大陆 香港 美国 日本） 美版依旧最低_Apple中国官网优惠_什么值得买. www.smzdm.com. [2018-08-05]. （原始内容存档于2018-08-05）.\n- ^ iSuppli拆解iPhone 4：硬體成本188美元 （页面存档备份，存于互联网档案馆）iThome每日新聞報文/范眠2010年06月29日\n- ^ 蘋